casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellant, v. Noggle, Appellee.

[Cite as State v. Noggle (2001), 91 Ohio St.3d 1280.]

(No. 00-1914 Submitted April 24, 2001 Decided June 6, 2001.) Russell B. Wiseman, Crawford County Prosecuting Attorney, and Clifford J. Murphy, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellant.

The cause is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently allowed.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur.
